*** 155,162
  A conforming implementation may have extensions (including
  additional library functions), provided they do not alter the
  behavior of any well-formed program.
! One example of such an extension is allowing identifiers to contain
! characters outside the basic source character set.
  Implementations are required to diagnose programs that use such
  extensions that are ill-formed according to this Standard.
  Having done so, however, they can compile and execute such programs.

--- 142,148 -----
