*** 863,897
  .CW int ,
  .CW unsigned
  .CW long
! .CW int .\*f
! .Fs
! A decimal integer literal with no suffix
! never has type
! .CW unsigned
! .CW int .
! Otherwise, for example, on an implementation where
! .CW unsigned
! .CW int
! values have 16
! bits and
! .CW unsigned
! .CW long
! values have strictly more than 17 bits,
! we would have
! .CW "-30000<0" ,
! .CW "-50000>0"
! (because
! .CW 50000
! would have type
! .CW unsigned
! .CW int ),
! and
! .CW "-70000<0"
! (because
! .CW 70000
! would have type
! .CW long ).
! .Fe
  If it is octal or hexadecimal and has no suffix, it has the first of these types in which its value can
  be represented:
  .CW int ,

